@remark ###################################################################
@node Introduction

@{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
-----------+

·DBatchFTP.thor is an ARexx script for converting Aminet download events in a
 Thor system to an email addressed to Demon Internet's Batch-FTP service.


@{fg shine}Why use it?@{fg text}
-----------+

·In my experience at least, when FTP'ing to an Aminet archive via Demon, data
 wasn't being sent through my modem all the time, like it was when I was
 downloading stuff from my home directory on Demon.

·Cutting out the extra link speeds things up for you, but also has another
 benefit: As Demon gets your files from Aminet quicker than you could, less time
 is spent accessing Aminet, and so the load on the site in question will be
 lessened, making other people's attempts at accessing Aminet more fruitful.


@{fg shine}What @{u}is@{uu} Batch-FTP anyway?@{fg text}
-------------------------+

·For those who aren't in the know, more information on Demon's Batch-FTP service
 can be found on Demon's web pages at:

 @{u}@{fg fill}Http://www.demon.net/services/ftp/batchftp.html@{uu}@{fg text}

@endnode
@remark ###################################################################
@node Installation

@{fg shine}Installation@{fg text}
------------+

·Copy DBatchFTP.thor to Thor's "rexx" directory ("Thor:rexx/")

·Copy this DbatchFTP.guide file to "Thor:Docs/" or wherever you keep the ARexx
 script docs on your system.

·Configure the ARexx menu in Thor to run "Thor:rexx/DBatchFTP.thor" from a free
 slot, if you have one ;)

·Now @{" configure " link Configuration} it!

@endnode
@remark ###################################################################
@node Requirements

@{fg shine}Requirements@{fg text}
------------+

·An Amiga
·THOR v2.4
·RexxMast running, as for all ARexx scripts.
·A Demon Internet dial-up account.


@{fg shine}Tested on@{fg text}
---------+

·Accelerated A1200 (via Blizzard 1220/4) with 6Mb RAM total, running Thor 2.4

@endnode
@remark ###################################################################
@node Configuration

@{fg shine}How to use it@{fg text}
-------------+

·First, load DBatchFTP.thor into your favourite editor, and @{b}check the variables
 set at the start of the script.@{ub} Change them if necessary, to suit your system.

·Create some download events in Thor, via the FileDatabase or NewFiles windows,
 in the usual way. (See Thor documentation for details on how to do this).

·@{b}DBatchFTP.thor picks up frozen download events *only*@{ub} - so, in the Events
 Window (RightAmiga-8), freeze the download events you want picked up by
 DBatchFTP.thor.

·Run DBatchFTP.thor from the ARexx menu in Thor. (Either from "Execute
 Script..." or configuring one of the menu options to run DBatchFTP.thor).

·If all goes well, you should be told how many events DBatchFTP.thor processed.
 Go back to your Events Window and you should see that a new Email event has been
 created!

·(You can edit the text of this email in the usual way, to get rid of files you
 later decide you don't want to retrieve via Batch-FTP.)

@endnode
@remark ###################################################################
@node GetInTouch

@{fg shine}Did it work?@{fg text}
------------+

·Whether it did or not, please give me some feedback. If nothing seems to be
 going right, however, and the cause of your problems is specific to
 DBatchFTP.thor, lemme know!

·My Email address for probs/feedback is as shown on the @{" contents page " link main}.

·@{b}NOTE:@{ub} If the problem is ARexx-related, ask on the Thor Mailing List or News
       Group. Seeing as this is my first ever attempt at ARexx coding, I'm
       unlikely to be able to answer ARexx queries :)

@endnode
