@node Me

@{fg shine}Who?@{fg text}
----+

·For those who are interested, here's a little background info on my humble
 existence. Some may already know parts of this from what I've said on the NG or
 ML, but allow me to fill in a few gaps...

·I'm twen... twen... tw... nineteen plus one :) years old, and am currently on
 my summer break before I head back to uni for my third and final year.

·I say "uni", but really, for the pedantic among you, it's "Southampton
 Institute of Higher Education". I'm sorry I don't attend a proper university
 like some, but then Southampton Uni don't do my course. Indeed, when I applied
 to do journalism, there were only 3 or 4 places offering it in the country!

·I've been an Amiga owner since, oooooooh, 19.. <counts on fingers> 1989/1990
 ish. Or whenever the A500+ came out. I had that for a good 3 or 4 years, before
 upgrading to my current A1200. Contrary to popular theory, the A500+'s
 brick-mouse served me well, and never went wrong in that whole time. Using the
 A1200 mouse was such a good experience in comparison that I've kept it to this
 very day, and it, too, has never gone wrong.

·I don't have a mouse mat. Not an official one anyway. I can't stand those
 horrible foam-backed A5 things. Especially the cloth-covered ones you get free
 with just about everything bar chewing gum. So, what? Do I keep the mouse on the
 desk? Use it on my knee? No! Announcing the ultimate mouse-mat! Free with
 compulsory education... The National Record of Achievement! It's perfect -
 slightly bigger than A4, nice grippy maroon leathery finish, and it even has
 some of those gold-plated L-shaped corner things on the front.

·Oh, and I also go under the pseudonyms "Newt" or "Turnip Fish". The latter
 comes from a song by The Sultans (formerly The Sultans of Ping F.C. and soon to
 be the ex-Sultans as they're breaking up *sniff*) of the same name. "Newt" comes
 from the phrase "p*ss*d as a newt". Enough said.

·One more thing: you can visit my web page at:

 @{fg fill}Http://www.nebula.demon.co.uk/@{fg text}

 for even more info about me, as well as some other stuff.

